parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
the "Hybrid System Warning" or "Safely Stop and Do Not Drive" message appears on the dashboard
the engine light comes on
the vehicle shakes or revs up and down
the brakes feel mushy
the power steering fails
the vehicle is unable to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to inconvenience, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
the lights and radio are activated but the engine does not start
the vehicle rolls when placed in gear
the battery is low or needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fire hazard can cause damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, as well as put the occupants at risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle catches fire
resulting in total loss of the vehicle and surrounding property.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floorboard
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brake light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle experiences a delayed reaction to braking
a grumbling noise is heard when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to go to the floorboard, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floorboard
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
low brake fluid level
loose brake fluid fittings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The message "Brake System Malfunction - Vehicle Will Turn Off for Safety" is displayed on the instrument panel
the vehicle turns off
the ABS module is faulty and needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it can also cause damage to other engine components.
symptoms: Abnormal knocking noise
sputtering
loss of acceleration
warning lights or messages on the dashboard
engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks and sludge buildup can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs or even engine failure. In some cases, it can also cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Low oil levels
no oil showing on the dipstick
oil light not illuminating
sludge buildup in the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Hybrid system malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose power or accelerate erratically, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Slow acceleration
launching forward after initial slow start
hybrid safety warning messages on the dashboard.
